HEADWORD: Lugsail
<hw>Lug"sail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
square sail bent upon a yard that hangs obliquely to the mast and is
raised or lowered with the sail.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

